<subSubSection id="C374652CFFA4FFCFD4CCF834081DF84E" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFA4FFCFD4CCF834081DF84E" blockId="89.[151,1437,1806,2013]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFA4FFCFD4CCF8340C16F82A" bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronymic in honor of the eminent arachnologist William Eberhard by his many contributions on ethology and evolution of the spiders, mainly focused on the spider webs evolution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
